OL,3,CInside Port Talbot's steelworks as
OL,4,Cblast furnace era draws to a close
OL,6,FIron and steel has been made in this
OL,7,Fway at Port Talbot for more than 70
OL,8,Fyears, but its days are now over.
OL,10,FWe watch the cauldron ablaze, as the
OL,11,Firon is made into steel. The light
OL,12,Ffrom the molten metal floods the dark
OL,13,Ffurnace with an orange glow. The heat
OL,14,Ffrom this process of Basic Oxygen
OL,15,FSteelmaking is intense as temperatures
OL,16,Fcan reach 1,700C.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G9/13
