OL,3,CInside Port Talbot's steelworks as
OL,4,Cblast furnace era draws to a close
OL,6,FHe says he is planning to retire to
OL,7,FSpain for the warmer weather and a
OL,8,Ffresh start.
OL,10,FAs we chat, a loud rumble clatters
OL,11,Fabove our heads. Without missing a
OL,12,Fbeat, Graham recognises it instantly.
OL,14,FIt's the sample lines going down to
OL,15,Fthe laboratory for analysis, he tells
OL,16,Fme. It has been the constant
OL,17,Fsoundtrack to Graham's working life.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G12/13
